HEADWORD: Cowbird
<hw>Cow"bird`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦etil⟧rd`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The cow blackbird (<spn>Molothrus ater</spn>),
an American starling. Like the European cuckoo, it builds no nest, but
lays its eggs in the nests of other birds; -- so called because
frequently associated with cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowblakes</ent>⟦br⟧
